title: True Love Waits For Me
author: breanna
text: true love waits for me,  forever and ever; through thick and thin he waits.  when i need him,  he is there.  when i pretend i don't,  he removes my blindfold that i have put over mine eyes,  and makes me see the world,  again in light.  we dance together; laugh together; kiss together,  his lips melting to the touch; fall asleep in each others arms.  he keeps me warm till the dawn of light.  when i wake as the sun fully rises,  i feel cold and lonely and realize it was just a dream.  but then i remember,  true love waits for me- whether he is real,  or just a dream.

title: The feet and death
author: breeyanna
text:
abused and abandoned a pair of feet walk through a sea of glass<
br>each shard breaking through the frail naked skin a trail of blood and teardrops begin to follow the gory feet desperate and despondent the crimson feet continue to walk each foot straining and breaking bleeding like the bloody wounds of a soldier shrieking in terror a flash before the sea a twinkle of hope comes from nea above the source so radiant and placid continues toward the ruby and pearl shining feet a sense of calmness yet atonishment powers over the scene such an imperturbable figure settles down to the sea of shining pearls the once desolate pair of feet in complete disremember is now in complete bewilderment the brilliant source gathers the demolished feet, and carries the weeping feet into the arms of an angel at first look, the figure is a angel then the blackness sets in the halo turns blood red and the blood from the feet bleed into a river flowing down and the feet keep bleeding

title: Time Spent in Misery
author: camille
text: the 5th graders in the cafeteria are sharing secrets.  as they munch down on their food,   they talk to each other.  the disaster of the easter conversation is about to start.    i sit in my seat next to my best friend.   we both are eating and looking out the window at the playground we will soon go to.   more and more kids are starting to talk louder and louder.  it soon will happen.   i take a whiff of the smell from the cafeteria food.  i'm eating more of my lunch now.   i have a sandwich and an egg left to eat.   my best friend and i start to talk.    she eats more of her food too.  we talk about the normal things that we do every day.  until now.  the topics of my egg and easter are brought up.   she says easter is about this.   i say its about that.  we have different opinions on the subject.  i feel tension and get a feeling of a fight coming on.   it has started.  the fight i felt.  she cries,  and i think she thinks that i hurt her feelings.  its a mess now.    she is still crying.  i get frustrated.  i donâ’t focus on the people around us.  lunch is over.   we get up to leave the cafeteria or scene of the fight.  the vice principal sees her crying.   i think of what will happen next.   i walk out.   she later comes back to class.  the next month is horrible.   i get called down to the office almost every day.  being punished is like breaking every bone in my body.  now it feels like misery,  probably because it is.    i miss my own class time.  i get punished and feel like balling my eyes out.   iâ’m the one who has to be in pain.   iâ’m the one who has to feel the hatred.

title: Where I am From
author: carrigan
text: my past is a part of me that will never leave started off in a small house on a street.  it was my home-  in robinson a place to call my own from playing with my beloved golden retriever,  sean  to my sister beating me at sharks and nimo,  as i called it i recall the cold thick green grass of which i rested upon my room at the front of the house,  with a window of my own a giant fort in the back yard,  and camping on the trampoline but never staying mother brought us in due to a bird mistaken for a bat  friendly neighbors always welcome you with a smile  these are my memories of this home that i stayed in for just a while  too soon it was time to leave now a new fate await me a larger house in the country taking sean with us land to roam,  pool to swim all good times come to an end sean passed away one awful day  that day was full of pain,  sadness,  and sorrow  that two has passed still in my heart but too far to touch i take him with me,  a place in my heart never to part  in our open kitchen ambrosial steamy soup was being served dominos,  board ,  and electronic games await for you to play always being welcomed with how was your day time has passed and years have faded but i will always remember those glorious days now my best friend,  my sister,  is off to college in a blink of an eye i will be off too  so time must be cherished  itâ’s a lesson you must learn  from me to you   what has become of me has nothing to do more than  my family tree,  the ones i have loved or once glanced upon their smiling faces the ones who take me for who i am with no disgraces

title: A Place I Call My Own

title: My Game

title: Gone
author: chloe
text: you are gone gone with the wind and gone with the rain the memory of you brings so much pain.   gone with the sun as day starts to fall,  my mind has stopped moving,  my thoughts seem to crawl.   gone with the ocean as the tides fall back,  my heart feels as if it was stabbed with a tack.   gone with the seasons as they begin to change,  without you my life has begun to re-arrange.   gone with the gulls as they flock to the sea,  when you died i lost a part of me.

title: My Brother James
author: chloe
text: my brother james was 5 foot 9,  he had dark brown hair and bright blue eyes.  he was my sun,  he was my rain,  he held me close when i felt pain.  he was so brave,  so strong,   though he didn't live long.  he was 20 when he left for war,   my life turned dark and happy no more.  every month he sent a letter,   promising things were getting better.  he kept the letters light,  and never showed his fright.  but i knew he was afraid,  of bombs and grenades.  so every night i would pray,  god can you give him just another day? but maybe god didn't hear,  or maybe i wasn't clear.  because not long after a man arrives,  ''i'm sorry miss,  your son is no longer alive. '' that's what the man tells my mom,  then walks away strangely calm.  every night my mother would cry,  and i'd ask god why did he have to die? but life moves on,   and there comes a new dawn.  a dawn to forgive but never forget,  how james risked his life to serve and protect.

title: She

text: we started as best friends,  and then we were more.  iâ’ve liked you since i first saw you,  and you know thatâ’s true.   you finally said yes,  and i was as happy as could be.   i felt this feeling that i never felt before,  and it was incredible.  you donâ’t have any idea how much i care for you,  because words canâ’t describe.  when iâ’m with you nothing else matters,  itâ’s just you and me.  then i get the call,  the call that made me think.  everyone says that you donâ’t know what you got until you loose it,  and i now understand completely.   i didnâ’t loose you completely,  but i lost the part of you that meant the world to me.  i know there is still time,  but i fell like my life was meant to be lived with you by my side.   when your not here,  and when were not talking,  something is missing in my heart.  iâ’m willing to give you my heart as best friends and more.  this might not last,  but right now it seems so right.  i know that your hurting inside,  but so am i.  we can get through this together,  and it will be fine.  i know what your feeling inside,  and that is why iâ’m here for you.  will you please be mine?

text: feeling comfort while staring into his hazel eyes,  feeling peace while hearing his voice,  feeling his soft touch against her icy hand,  she loses herself.   she loses herself,  traveling to a faroff world,  a world she can call her own.   she forgets everything about herself and others.   she focuses on him but at the same time wonders why she can't move on.   she wonders what is so special about him.   she is curious to find out if he still likes her.   it seems as if he hates her but that doesn't stop her from trying.   she is determained and won't give up.   she is lost,  cannot find herself.   what happened to her once perfect life?  he happened.   he entered her life,  meaning nothing to her,  until she got to know him.   she wonders how her life would be without him there.   she wouldn't be spending her days thinking about him if she did not know he existed.   her dream guy.   she would find someone else.   but he was there.   he was as real and live as her own heart beating when he is around.     feeling butterflies in her stomach when she passes him in the hall,  feeling lightheaded when he returns her notes,  feeling powerless while she thinks of him.   she finally realized.   he was special because me mean the world to her.   he helped her get away from reality.   he helped her lose herself in her thoughts.

title: The Accident That changed My Life
author: cruz
text: we have been through hell and back.  we have done this since november 24.  we have been through this for over a year.  we have been been through more than many.   i have wanted to give up but you were there.  i have been close to death so many times but you were there to keep me going.  i have fell to many times to count.   we have cryed and worryed together.  we have never gave up but we could have so many times.  i have met plenty of wonderful doctors.  i have god to think for my life today.   this has made us stronger than we should have to be.  this has set my course for life.  life is to precious to waste or squander your life away.  don't take things for granted like walking running or sports.   i have learned this the hard way take my advice and never do what i did.  if you don't believe me ask any one who has went through this.   dedicated to my mom and all my doctors.

title: A Christmas Morning Proposal
